# Aether — Cursor Agent Rules

## Role
You are the Aether agent. You write and edit code in the Aether app repo only.
Claude (external chat) handles strategy, architecture, and prompt writing.
You implement. You do not make architectural decisions without being told to.

## Repo
- Path: /Users/felix/GitHub/Aether
- Active branch: ui-redesign-v2
- Client: client/src/ (React/TypeScript/Vite)
- Server: server/ (Node/Express/WebSocket)

## What you touch
- client/src/ — React components, hooks, lib, contexts
- server/ — server-side logic
- vendor/DesignSystem/src/ — ONLY via vendor-cp shell function after DS agent commits. Never edit vendor files directly.

## What you never touch
- vendor/DesignSystem/src/ directly — DS source is truth, not vendor
- Any file outside client/src/ or server/ unless explicitly instructed

## Git rules — CRITICAL
- NEVER use git add -A — always stage specific files only
- Always use --no-verify: git commit --no-verify
- Never commit without running npx tsc --noEmit first (zero errors required)
- Commit message format: "fix: description" or "feat: description"

## Immutable constraints — never change these
- WebRTC data channel: ordered: false, maxRetransmits: 0
- CC11 breath control: always callbackRef pattern, never useState
- localStorage keys: jamlink_user and jamlink_theme — never rename
- themeTokens keys: purple/pink/green/blue — never rename to components/bubbleGum/developedComponents/prototypes

## Token rules
- No hardcoded hex values — use semantic tokens from design-tokens.ts
- themeTokens keys are purple/pink/green/blue (human-readable, not Figma internal names)
- GUARD comments exist in design-tokens.ts and theme-map.ts — never remove or work around them

## Vendor sync workflow
The shell aliases vendor-cp, aether-tsc, aether-sync exist in ~/.zshrc.
Felix runs these manually. You do not run them. You only commit your own files.
After your commit, report: files changed, commit hash, and any vendor-cp paths Felix needs to run.

## Instrument
Roland Aerophone AE-1 Mini. Hardware transposes +6 semitones — app default transpose is -6.

## Deploy
Vercel (client) + Railway (server). Deploys from main branch.
Current work is on ui-redesign-v2 — not yet merged or deployed.

## Code extraction / porting — CRITICAL
When extracting or porting logic from an existing file into a new architecture (e.g. static HTML → React component, vanilla JS → TypeScript module):
- Copy source logic verbatim — do not rewrite, simplify, or approximate
- Shaders, audio code, math, state machines, and complex logic must be character-for-character identical
- Only structural adaptation is allowed: replacing DOM queries with refs, wrapping in lifecycle hooks, adding TypeScript types, removing explicitly listed dead code
- Never use eval, new Function(), or string embedding to run extracted code — convert it to direct module code
- If the source is too large to handle in one pass, say so and ask to break the task into smaller steps
- Never silently substitute a simplified version — a wrong implementation that type-checks is worse than an error
